  - <ID>k__BackingField: 47fd3a0a-6847-47fe-9056-2d540eabf519
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName7dash2
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: 79462f47-8e45-406c-9684-d092eb6edc9c
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 4374.4, y: 396.80002}
    <Text>k__BackingField: Well, those who rise to the upper middle income bracket
      and beyond
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: 605fcf6a-6f7e-4ab5-8a27-f84401ca3cb4
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName9
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: d51fd9dd-a3d9-453d-bcef-caa84ec50390
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 5709.6, y: 93.6}
    <Text>k__BackingField: 'Additionally, wealthier and priviledge men tends to have
      more freedom to choose what kind of masculinity they choose to potray. '
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: 33026cf5-cb45-44d0-bc75-c968ad7d5807
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName11
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: 450db2de-dcbf-40cf-9be6-7a8dd8f9ec1b
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 7158.4, y: 121.6}
    <Text>k__BackingField: Then this begs the question, how does this tie in between
      capitalism, universities and the rise of contemporary masculinity amongst men
      coming from such institutions? How exactly does wealthy men Americans play
      ino this?
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: 450db2de-dcbf-40cf-9be6-7a8dd8f9ec1b
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName12
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: 3d1be908-f800-4b80-b4de-86ee6e06e008
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 7895.2, y: 146.40001}
    <Text>k__BackingField: The answer is in fraternities.
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: 3d1be908-f800-4b80-b4de-86ee6e06e008
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName13
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: a42fa2a0-2793-4e34-b6db-e9f808f430ff
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 8425.6, y: 155.20001}
    <Text>k__BackingField: Fraternities are a type of student run club in American
      universities and colleges for male students. Many wealthy and powerful students
      tend to be in fraternities. According to Berkley, "80 percent of Fortune 500
      executives, 76 percent of U.S. senators and congressmen, 85 percent of Supreme
      Court justices, and all but two presidents since 1825 have been fraternity
      men"
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: a42fa2a0-2793-4e34-b6db-e9f808f430ff
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName14
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: d473dd18-7f3d-4c6e-b8a4-c187676ec7c9
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 9144, y: 172.8}
    <Text>k__BackingField: As such, it can be seen that fraternities are a way for
      men to climb the social ladder and forge connections that can help them in
      the future. In fact, researchers have found that they help boost a person's
      income by 36%
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: d473dd18-7f3d-4c6e-b8a4-c187676ec7c9
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName15
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: 
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 9853.6, y: 172.8}
    <Text>k__BackingField: As we established earlier that wealthier americans tend
      to display hybrid masculinity, men who seek to increase their social standing
      regardless of their wealth would therefore need to share such beliefs as well,
      thereby normalizing this form of masculinity in university and also explains
      why more college educated men would then adop it
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
    <RightSprites>k__BackingField: []
    <IsChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <IsRememberChoiceNode>k__BackingField: 0
    <RememberSO>k__BackingField: {fileID: 0}
    ChoiceSO:
    - {fileID: 0}
    BackgroundImage: {fileID: 7761469775469319506, guid: d8e73123fbee7f64697f411872792092, type: 3}
  - <ID>k__BackingField: d51fd9dd-a3d9-453d-bcef-caa84ec50390
    <Name>k__BackingField: DialogueName10
    <Choices>k__BackingField:
    - <Text>k__BackingField: New Choice
      <NodeID>k__BackingField: 33026cf5-cb45-44d0-bc75-c968ad7d5807
    <GroupID>k__BackingField: 
    <Position>k__BackingField: {x: 6453.6, y: 93.6}
    <Text>k__BackingField: Unsurprisingly, wealthy americans that go to universities
      tend to display such forms of hybrid masculinity
    <Actions>k__BackingField: []
    <LeftSprites>k__BackingField:
    - {fileID: 6800915032177342135, guid: 97dbcf3c2e2539d489c7150e0fe63bd8, type: 3}
